Ive always driven by this place on a daily basis, so today I decided to finally try it. This was my experience. We were greeted by Alejandra who had a great attitude seating us, and I chose to sit with my friend in the left corner due to the amount of shade. Overall the environment I got from my first seating was great, but Im not sure I just got this sense that the tables weren’t cleaned enough, so I just avoided it as much as i could. The menu seemed very organized and not cluttered which I was very fond of. Alot of choices to choose from, what I ended up ordering was a Classic Shrimp, The portage, and The Tux tacos. My god the Classic Shrimp was incredible, it was so good I had to order another one at the end of my meal. The Tux from my understanding of the image online it has two scallops not one, and the combination with the potato had an overwhelming flavor so I didn’t really know what was going on. So I don’t really recommend getting that one. The portage I was not expecting a whole jalapeño and that is awesome! The steak was tender and seasoning was perfect, I still ate it despite the heat factor it was expected. I loved it and will order it forsure next time. Presentation of each taco was fantastic, as you can see I took a picture for my instagram story. So I end this review on a good note. Believe the hype.

I'm so happy we've found this little gem of a taco spot in Portage Park, and a little bummed that it took me so long. Better late than never! I went in on a Tuesday, and tried their 3 taco special w/ rice & beans for $13.  The jibarito taco - a slice of steak on a plantain taco shell with lettuce, tomato, & garlic aioli. The chunk of steak looked big, and I was worried it would be chewy, but when I but in it was melt-in-your-mouth tender. The flavor was on point, and I loved the plantain shell!  The chorizo con papas taco - 1st, the handmade tortillas they use are fantastic! They start with a generous layer of spicy chorizo, followed by their potato casserole, and finally sour cream. This is a delicious and hearty taco, for sure.  The sirena taco - Bacon wrapped shrimp with pickled red cabbage, Chile aioli, & Pico de gallo. A lot of the time when I have bacon wrapped shrimp, the bacon overpowers the shrimp. Not the case here. The ingredient ratio delivered the perfect flavor from all of the ingredients.  The interior is nice, and the staff was super helpful and courteous. I love the Frida mural out front! I can't wait to come back and try the other tacos, but next time I'll skip the rice & beans. They were good, but I'd rather save the stomach space for more tacos. They are also BYOB!

Always consistently fresh and delish!  So I’m a little confused about things I’ve been reading out here.  Ok- this is a taco place. Kind of fast, but made to order, so sometimes it takes a little bit.  This is Not fine dining, it’s casual- and I’m wondering what kind of stellar service people get at other fast food taco places, because elsewhere I’m lucky if I get a smile and a thank you. Tatas always smiles and thanks me and asks me if I need anything which is again WAAAAY more than I get elsewhere. The CORN tortillas are handmade from fresh masa.  You can see them making them- soooo I’m confused about a review which is why I had to comment.  If you ask, they’ll tell you the flour tortillas are delivered fresh every morning.  FYI, burritos come on a big FLOUR tortilla.  I’ve had everything on the menu, and I have to remark, the Chile  rellenos are HUGE and won’t fit in a taco, so they cut it in half.  It’s really hearty and filling -actually one of my favs being an awesome vegetarian taco option.  Also,  I just returned from a trip to MX and I can’t wait to get back in to Tatas because even in MX I couldn’t find food as good as this.  I’ve also seen comments about the cost of drinks- and guess what they’re pretty much the same everywhere that serves bottles and higher quality food.  I even think the fast food place next door charges about 3 bucks for a fountain drink, so come on people....The $1.50 taco place is down the street....oh - and burritos do take a little longer - but do the math, they cook your food fresh every time. Other places give you god knows what meat that’s been sitting around for the better portion of the day.  So I say keep on doing what you’re doing Tatas and ignore the morons! I LOVE my food fresh without any junk.  No they’re not typical - THANK GOD!!  Frankly, I think people are hypercritical because it’s owned by a woman.  Maybe people don’t expect a dude to mommy them when they go buy a taco.
Great service, people and food.

Cashier said the tortillas was hand made which I don’t think they was cold I tried 3 different tacos they was not freshly made for the Chile relleno they only give you half of of the whole Chile relleno that was weird, al pastor was pre-made pork just heated on microwave, asada was ok but cold I like my food hot. My son order a steak burrito and it had more lettuce than anything he was looking for the steak it was also cold never again yucks.

The only reason I’m giving this place a 3 star instead of 4 or even 5 is because, they need to be more organized. I ordered a burrito for carry out which by the way was good, no complaints about that and I waited for about 25 mins until I saw they were bringing the food of a party of 6 that ordered after me. Then, I got up and I went to the pick up side and I asked about my ordered, the nice lady who was taking care of the orders, taking them to the tables and cleaning them had it sitting there for I don’t know how long and I asked her “I thought you were going to call out my name” since they asked for my name when I placed my order. The place is nice, they are friendly, they have board games to keep you entertained until your food arrives, fair prices. They only need to be more attentive overall, especially for the people that order carry out and call out their names. I would recommend it, and will be going back.

My family used to go to a taco place a few blocks from our house but one day it upped and vanished. No warning that it was going to close. The other day we found Tatas Tacos. My daughter had the plain Jane with chicken. Everything was delicious. It wasn't spicy and I think from the reviews that are a bit negative claiming food is bland (read from Yelp), I believe they were expecting spiciness. If I read correctly, they are still fairly new. They have potential to grow and build on their menu. I can see the possibility of them adding to their menu the ability to change the level of heat to accommodate those who want a stronger bolder flavor and still offer mild flavor for those who want a bit a spice. Also, torrejas for dessert was yummy and I look forward to having it again.

This is going to be one of my favorite spots for sure 👌👍👍 the customer service is 100% , they are very friendly, welcoming and caring. We tried almost everything on the menu and loved it all. They care so much about customer satisfaction, they use recycled utensils and various different items. They have different recycling bins for the costumer to recycle ♻️ and there are a couple of tables outside to have a nice date out with a significant other or your loved ones. They welcome dogs outside with snacks and water for them to hydrate if needed, it is a nice spot to stop by with your dog to take a little rest and relax. The inside of the restaurant offers nice big tables, plenty of sitting for a big family and the also have big lottery’s cards for you to play after a good meal. We tried playing it while waiting for the food but it came out so quick that we couldn’t start the game that’s how quick the service is.. So I would say that’s it is definitely a game to play after the wonderful food, and just hand out for a little bit. The decorations of the place makes it stand out from everything around it so much that you won’t have trouble finding it, from the street block to the walls. Yum yum yum!! This place is awesome! Amazing vibe, yummy fresh food, very helpful  and friendly staff!! I’ve been here 3 times this last week because everything I tried was so wonderful I wanted to try more!! And there’s still more to try- I’m coming back!! The reason I’m posting this is every time I come, it’s consistently good and I felt I needed to say something after reading some of the things out here.  Please note - this is a self service restaurant.  It’s pretty clear, and honestly, I don’t know how anyone could miss the signs that clearly say “order here” and “pick up here”.  Thr owner once said - it’s kind of like a Panera set up....  (but not the food) The food quality is high and fresh to its not a typical fast taqueria.  Unlike other places - The meat isn’t chopped to death so you don’t see all the fat, and the guacamole is not mixed - I like it/ I like to see how much avocado I’m getting and I like that there aren’t fillers.  Lean fresh meats, out of this world tortillas and fresh veggies .... the rice and beans are amazing too!! The shrimp tacos are great and so is the pork.  Just a great place- and oh- I almost forgot - it’s BYOB!!!!
